    "attributes": {
        "action": "Retain Bus passes and tv licenses for older people.",
        "additional_details": "\u201cIn the last few decades, loneliness has escalated from personal misfortune into a social epidemic. More and more of us live alone. We work at home more. We spend a greater part of our day alone than we did 10 years ago. It sometimes feels like our best friend is the smartphone.\u201d\r\nLoneliness is not exclusive to older people, but this group, in my experience (as a Housing Professional) are impacted at a much higher level.",
        "background": "The provision of a bus pass and tv license are a major lifeline for many older people who are subject to isolation and loneliness. The proposal from \r\nHouse of Lords Select Committee is in direct contradiction to the Governments stated concern about loneliness and isolation.",
